<br>
The year 2309 was the end of the Second Imperial Age.  100 years prior, strong nationalist governments expanded into the depths of the galaxy using a new technology called SIM (Subspace Induction Matrix.)  Humans spread across the galaxy, colonizing and developing over 350 planetary bodies and inhabiting 310 starsystems.  New technologies develop and society flourishes with art and literature. This 100 years was also called the Second Great Rennaissance. This awesome development was fueled by the Solar Mining Corporation eternally lusting for more profits and resources.  Then humans found Oberon.<br>
<br>
GSS 311 (Oberon) was an exceptionally rare gem in the crown of the Confederation. 12 planets, 28 moons, three asteroid belts chaulked full of rare and precious minerals were discovered, orbiting a star much like Earth's.  Millions of SMC prospectors flocked to Oberon Prime (a desert world that is the 4th planet)  Suddenly all contact was lost.<br>
<br>
A steel Tsunami poured out of the gateway leading to Oberon, destroying everything in its path.<br>
<br>
It was soon determined that there was no negotiation with this mysterious race. Humanity stepped into the path of a highly agressive enemy who used their strength in numbers to overcome the unprepared humans.<br>
<br>
The race was merciless, their army was massive, their being was Artifical.<br>
<br>
Humanity must now fight to resist the onslaught.<br>
Its Flesh and Blood Vs. Silicon and Steel....<br>
<br>
Comments? Questions? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otakulad>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/10/03 6:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Steel Tsunami (unless you got a better title)</span><hr size=1> Thus 'far-flung' sci-fi ones (way in the future) are really tough for me to comment on. You have no real idea of how far technology will have gone. I can't even begin to imagine the unconventional weapondry...<br>
<br>
I suppose the thing to do would be to try and analyze the new alien species. Why do they attack? What exactly are they? How do they propagate?<br>
<br>
Like I said, far-future is tough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scorpius@polykarbonbbs>Scorpius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/11/03 12:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> answers</span><hr size=1> The race of artifical intellegence (which is unnamed) was built by an unknown species.  The AI are like viruses, they move into an area, consume all the resources then move on.  They digest whole planets by spinning massive webs across rocky planets until the surface is completely converted and the interior is mined hollow then the structure is dismantled.  This process takes thousands of years to fully consume a planet.  But as resources are being taken, they reproduce by self replication.  They build more of themselves to spread and control other systems throughout the galaxy.<br>
<br>
Their purpose for attacking is because humans or other sentient life is a competitor and competition is not good for the strength of the species.<br>
<br>
This is based on an idea by a famous scince fiction writer who said that a race of artificial intellegence could completely dominate a galaxy in less than a million years.<br>
Using conventional methods of transportation. (slower than light speed.) But since they travel faster than light, it could take much less time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otakulad>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/11/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: answers</span><hr size=1> Actually, in one of Kurt Vonnegurt's short stories, he also developed the idea of nanites that were capable of digesting anything and using what they digested to propagate themsleves. This &quot;grey sludge&quot; just grew and grew as it consumed more and more...<br>
<br>
AI-beings as mineral harvesters. I see, they organize minerals and elements down to their simplest form for ease-of use? Maybe the end product was to be transferred back to the home base.<br>
<br>
What might be cool is if the species that originated them had some sort of control built in, but after countless multiplications, there was an error. The new, slightly-mutated steel beings could not be controlled. What's worse, they recognized their 'parents' as alien life and attacked them. They would then turn on their creators... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scorpius@polykarbonbbs>Scorpius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/11/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> yep</span><hr size=1> Exactly what I had in mind! I was going to mention nanotechnology but then it would be too easy to wipe out humanity with an artifical plague or attacking a planet with some mechanical spores. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otakulad>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/13/03 9:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yep</span><hr size=1> They would have to be fission-powered...<br>
